  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><p><strong>Table of Demonstratives</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><br></td><td style=\"width: 13.8587%;\"><p>this</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>that</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>that over there</p></td><td><p>question word</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>thing (not person)</p></td><td style=\"width: 13.8587%;\"><p>これ</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>それ</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>あれ</p></td><td><p>なん</p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<p>place</p></td><td style=\"width: 13.8587%;\"><p>ここ</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\">&nbsp;そこ&nbsp;</td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>あそこ</p></td><td><p>どこ</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>noun modifier</p></td><td style=\"width: 13.8587%;\"><p>この N</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>その N</p></td><td style=\"width: 16.1111%;\"><p>あの N</p></td><td><p>なんの N</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>1. この /その / あの can also be used in front of person nouns<br>2. Polite demonstratives こちら etc are the equivalent to both これ and ここ<br>3. &nbsp;All place demonstratives such as どこ, ここ can be combined with &lsquo;の N&rsquo; like &lsquo;どこのれいぞうこですか&rsquo;, you can see this in Day 3 lessons</p><p>You can download this cheat sheet <a class=\"fr-file\" href=\"../../pdfs/shared/Table_of_demonstratives.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">here,</a></p></div>",
